<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Find vulnerable packages on the fly</b></p><p>With the bundled <span class="control">Package Checker</span> plugin, IntelliJ IDEA can highlight vulnerable packages in your Maven and Gradle project on the fly.</p><p>Make sure that the <span class="control">Vulnerable declared dependency</span> inspection is enabled in <span class="control">Settings | Editor | Inspections | Security</span> and open your build file. Vulnerable dependencies will be highlighted right in the editor.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/package_checker_inspection.png" alt="Package Checker inspection" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>